ce:section.ce:para:
The cross-section morphology of PVA and PVA composite films were observed by SEM (Fig. 5
                        ). Compared with pure PVA film, the PVA composite films with CQDs showed a more roughness surface without obvious aggregation, implying that the CQDs had a good compatibility with PVA and produced a strong interfacial interaction between CQDs and PVA. The effects of MPD-CQDs, MPD-HPP-CQDs and MPD-PA-CQDs on the mechanical properties of PVA films were investigated by tensile tests, and the results were shown in Fig. 5e and Table 1
                        . The tensile strength and elongation at break of the pure PVA film were 67.0 MPa and 183.1%, respectively. After the addition of MPD-CQDs, the tensile strength of MPD-CQDs-PVA composite film decreased slightly, and the elongation at break increased to 254.3%. When the addition amount of MPD-HPP-CQDs/MPD-PA-CQDs was in the range of 5–10%, the elongation at break of PVA-CQDs composite films were enhanced and the tensile strength almost maintained. It might also be explained by the reason that the hydrogen bonding force formed between PVA and CQDs, which was greater than that of the single PVA intermolecular and intramolecular hydrogen bonding interaction [33].
